You are an experienced Chrome Extension developer.

Create a full Chrome Extension (Manifest V3) named:
**"FB Group Collector - Safe Mode"**

---

## 🎯 Goal
I want this extension to:
1. Automatically scroll (auto-scroll) a Facebook Group page with random delays to avoid detection or account blocking.
2. On each scroll, extract the visible posts from the DOM, including:
   - Post link (if available)
   - Author name
   - Author profile link
   - Post content (text only)
   - List of image URLs (only links, no image downloads)
3. Store the collected posts temporarily in the background service worker.
4. When the user clicks “Stop & Download JSON”, export all collected posts to a JSON file named `facebook_posts_<timestamp>.json`.

---

## ⚙️ Key Features
- A popup UI that allows user to set:
  - `minDelay` (in seconds)
  - `maxDelay` (in seconds)
  - `maxScrolls` (maximum scroll count)
- Two buttons:
  - **Start (safe)** → sends a command to the content script to start auto-scrolling
  - **Stop & Download JSON** → stops the crawler and triggers JSON download
- Popup should display real-time progress:
  - Running / Stopped status
  - Current scroll count
  - Number of posts collected

---

## 🧩 Project structure
Create these 4 main files:

### 1. `manifest.json`
- `"manifest_version": 3`
- Permissions: `["activeTab", "scripting", "downloads", "storage"]`
- Host permissions: `["https://www.facebook.com/*", "https://mbasic.facebook.com/*"]`
- Background: `service_worker` → `background.js`
- Action: `popup.html`

---

### 2. `popup.html`
- Contains inputs for `minDelay`, `maxDelay`, `maxScrolls`
- Buttons: **Start** and **Stop & Download**
- Displays status updates (running state, scroll count, collected count)
- Saves configuration in `chrome.storage.local`
- Sends commands to content script and background via `chrome.runtime.sendMessage`

---

### 3. `content.js`
- Listens for `"start"` and `"stop"` commands from popup
- On `"start"`:
  - Scrolls page with `window.scrollTo({ behavior: "smooth" })`
  - Waits a random delay between `minDelay` and `maxDelay` seconds before each scroll
  - Stops when reaching `maxScrolls` or when receiving `"stop"`
  - After each scroll, extract post data from DOM using selectors like:
    - `[role="article"]`
    - `div[data-pagelet^="FeedUnit_"]`
  - Extract:
    - Post link
    - Author name
    - Author profile link
    - Post text content
    - Image URLs from `<img>` tags (only valid URLs)
- Sends data to background with:
  ```js
  chrome.runtime.sendMessage({ type: "save_posts", data: posts });
